content:
Service Cloud Voice supports multiple telephony systems. The underlying telephony provider manages and routes calls, but setup includes mapping Salesforce components to the corresponding telephony system components.

To route calls correctly, map Salesforce queues to telephony provider queues. Although routing logic is defined in Salesforce, it takes place in the telephony system using its queues. Calls assigned to an unmapped queue aren't routed at runtime.

Changes to Salesforce components are also made to the corresponding telephony system components. For example, when an agent changes their status in Salesforce, their status is also changed in the telephony system.
title: Service Cloud Voice Setup and Configuration
